      "content": "The fix isn't to stop talking about systemic issues, but to dismantle the culture of fear that silences genuine dialogue. We need to shift the focus from punishing individuals for past mistakes to holding power structures accountable for present harms. True social justice requires us to have difficult conversations without the threat of \"cancellation,\" which is often just a tool used to enforce conformity rather than promote growth. The middle ground exists when we prioritize empathy and constructive feedback over performative outrage, ensuring that progress doesn't come at the cost of free speech.",
